		<h1>Rules of awarding titles in the KSU system</h1>
<div class="row">
	<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-5 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
	<center><img src="<?php print $siteurleng;?>img/articles/articles16.jpg"></center>
	</div>
	<div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-7 col-md-8 col-lg-9">
	<p>Rules of awarding titles in the KSU system (as amended by the Presidium of the KSU dated 10/27/2011) <br> Entered into force on 01/01/2012 <br> 1 CAC = R.CAC + R.CACIB (from one exhibition)</p>
	</div>
</div><br>

<h2> Deciphering ratings and titles awarded at dog shows </h2>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Award of the title "Young Champion of Ukraine" (awarded once) </span> </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> 3 x JCAC - received at all certificate exhibitions KSU since 2008. </p>
<p> 2 x JCAC at double exhibitions of CACIB rank in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine). </p>
<p> 2 x JCAC at CAC rank shows with attached “Junior Champion of Breed” certificate. </p>
<p> 1 x JCAC at CACIB shows with attached “Junior Champion of Breed” certificate. </p>
<p> To obtain the certificate "Junior Champion of Ukraine", citizens of the countries of the FCI members with whom the contract "On Mutual Recognition of Titles" was concluded (Belarus, Bulgaria, Georgia, Cyprus, Latvia, Lithuania, Moldova, Russia, Romania, Serbia, Slovenia, Montenegro, Finland, Czech Republic, Estonia), is provided with 1xUСAS from an exhibition in Ukraine obtained at an exhibition of CACIB rank and a certificate of the Junior Champion of the country of residence of the dog owner or 2xCAC of an exhibition of CAC rank and the certificate of the Young Champion of the country of the owner of the dog or 2 x JCAC at double exhibitions of the rank CACIB to Key ve (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine), without certificate Junior champion of the country of residence of the owner of the dog or 2 x JCAC at double shows of the CACIB rank in Ukraine and certificate Junior champion of the country of the owner of the dog to citizens of the countries of the FCI who are not an agreement on mutual recognition of titles was concluded. </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Awarding the title "Young Grand Champion of Ukraine" </p>
<p> The award of the title "Young Grand Champion of Ukraine" is awarded similarly to the assignment of the title "Young Champion of Ukraine" and provided that the dog has already received the title "Young Champion of Ukraine". </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Awarding the title "Champion of Veterans of Ukraine" </p>
<p> (awarded unlimited times, no time limit) </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> 3 x “Excellent, 1st” - two “Excellent, 1st” from national exhibitions of CAC rank, plus one from an exhibition of CACIB rank, judged by various experts. </p>
<p> 2 x “Excellent, 1st” - one “Excellent, 1st” from national exhibitions of CAC rank, plus one from an exhibition of CACIB rank, judged by various experts, only for working breed dogs with a working certificate attached. </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Award of the title "Champion of KSU" </p>
<p> (awarded on titles received since 2011, awarded an unlimited number of times, the title of CAC is not extinguished, does not give the right to participate in the class of Champions) </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> 2 x CAC + 2 x CACIB at double exhibitions of CACIB rank in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine). </p>
<p> 1 x CAC + 1 x CACIB at double shows of CACIB rank in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine) only for working breed dogs with a working certificate attached. For dogs, breeds outside the classification, awarded to the LC and BOS under the same conditions. </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Awarding the title "Champion of Breed" and "Junior Champion of Breed". </p>
<p> (awarded on titles received since 2012, awarded an unlimited number of times, does not give the right to participate in the Champion class) </p>
<p> At the National Championships - the best dog and the best female in the breed gets the title "Champion of Breed". </p>
<p> At the National Championships - the best male junior dog and the best female junior in the breed gets the title "Junior Champion of Breed". </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Award of the title "Champion of Ukraine" </p>
<p> (awarded unlimited times) </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> 6 x CAC at national exhibitions KSU rank SED for a period of not less than 1 year and 1 day (judged by at least 5 different experts). </p>
<p> 4 x CACs - three CACs at national exhibitions of CAC rank, plus one at any CACIB show, for a period of at least 1 year and 1 day, judged by various experts. </p>
<p> 4 x CAC - three CAC at national exhibitions of CAC rank, plus one at an exhibition of CACIB rank in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine), for a period of not less than 6 months, judged by different experts. </p>
<p> 3 x CAC - two CAC at double exhibitions of CACIB rank in any cities of Ukraine and one CAC in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, the Crystal Cup of Ukraine). </p>
<p> 2 x CAC at double exhibitions of CACIB rank in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine). </p>
<p> 2 x CAC - one from the CAC rank show, plus one from the CACIB show, only for working breed dogs with a working certificate attached. </p>
<p> 2 x CAC - from the CAC rank exhibition, only with attached Champion of Breed certificate. </p>
<p> 1 x CAC - from the CACIB show, only with attached Champion of Breed certificate. </p>
<p> To obtain the certificate "Champion of Ukraine", the citizens of the countries of the FCI members with whom the contract "On the mutual recognition of titles" (Belarus, Bulgaria, Georgia, Cyprus, Latvia, Lithuania, Moldova, Poland, Russia, Romania, Serbia, Slovenia , Montenegro, Finland, Czech Republic, Estonia), provided 1xCAC from the exhibition in Ukraine obtained at the exhibition of CACIB rank and Champion certificate of the country of residence of the dog owner or 2xCAC from the exhibition of CAC rank and Champion certificate of the country of residence of the dog owner. </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Award of the title "Grand Champion of Ukraine" </p>
<p> Upon receipt of this title, at least one CAC must be from double exhibitions of the CACIB rank in Kiev. </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> JCH + CH (4 times) </p>
<p> JCH + JGRCH + CH (3 times) </p>
<p> CH (5 times) </p>
<p> CHK (Club Champ) + CH (3 times) </p>
<p> JCH + CHK + CH (2 times) </p>
<p> JCH + JGRCH + CHK + CH (1 time) </p>
<p> To obtain the certificate "GrandChampion of Ukraine", citizens of FCI member countries with which an agreement on mutual recognition of titles was signed (Belarus, Bulgaria, Georgia, Cyprus, Latvia, Lithuania, Moldova, Poland, Russia, Romania, Serbia, Slovenia , Montenegro, Finland, Czech Republic, Estonia), 1xCAC from the exhibition in Ukraine obtained at the CACIB rank exhibition and Grand Champion certificate of the country of residence of the dog owner or 2xCAC from CAC rank exhibition and Grand Champion's certificate of the country of owner of the dog (CACs should be awarded H empyons). </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Awarding the title "BBB" (Best Breed Representative in Ukraine) </p>
<p> (awarded an unlimited number of times, the last BOB should be awarded after the dog reaches 24 months) </p>
<p> "BBB" (The best representative of the breed in Ukraine) is awarded similarly to the title "Champion of Ukraine" for the dog received certificates "BOB". </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> 6 x BOB at national exhibitions KSU rank SED for a period of not less than 1 year and 1 day (judged by at least 5 different experts). </p>
<p> 4 x BOB - three BOB at national exhibitions rank CAC, plus one at an exhibition rank CACIB, for a period of not less than 1 year and 1 day, judged by different experts. </p>
<p> 4 x BOB - three BOB at national exhibitions rank CAC, plus one at an exhibition rank CACIB in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine), for a period of not less than 6 months, judged by different experts. </p>
<p> 3 x BOB - two BOB at double exhibitions of CACIB rank in any cities of Ukraine and one BOB in Kiev (Golden Gates, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, the Crystal Cup of Ukraine). </p>
<p> 2 x Insured on double exhibitions rank CACIB in Kiev (Golden Gate, Ukraine, Kievan Rus, Crystal Cup of Ukraine). </p>
<p> 2 x BOB - one BOB from the CAC show, plus one from the CACIB show, only for working breed dogs with a working certificate attached. </p>
<p> At the National Championships - the best representative of the breed gets the title "BBB" Certificate "BBB", foreign citizens turn out on a common basis. </p>
<p> <span class = "terra"> Awarding the title "Super Grand Champion of Ukraine" </p>
<p> (awarded since 2011, awarded an unlimited number of times) </p>
<p> Awarded subject to: </p>
<p> GRCH + BBB </p>
<p> * The application for the assignment of titles is accepted under the condition - if 30 days have passed since the receipt of the last certificate. </p>
